comments.text: D67N is a non-polymorphic TAM associated with low-level resistance to AZT and d4T. When present with other TAMs, it contributes reduced susceptibility to ABC, ddI, and TDF.
K70R causes intermediate resistance to AZT and possibly low-level resistance to D4T, DDI, ABC and TDF.
K219Q/E are accessory TAMS associated with reduced susceptibility to AZT and possibly d4T.
